03/03/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer vetoed a controversial law Wednesday (2 March) that granted amnesty to students expelled from universities, including women dismissed for wearing traditional headscarves in class. 
Parliament had approved the measure in late February. 
The president said it violated the Constitution.
In other news Wednesday, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan wrapped up a visit to Ethiopia aimed at boosting economic and trade ties. 
He travels to South Africa Thursday. 
(NTV - 03/03/05; TurkishPress, AFP, NTV - 02/03/05)
